                    <history>
                        <provenance>The manuscript had very probably belonged to a church in the
                            <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC3577Gondar">Gondar</placeName> area, possibly  <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC2248DabraB">Dabra Bǝrhān Śǝllāse</placeName>, 
                            as a church Dabra Bǝrhān is mentioned in <ref target="#a5"/>, from where it was taken by
                            <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS9430Tewodros">Tewodros</persName> and brought to <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0101MadhaneAlam">Madḫāne ʿĀlam</placeName>. It was then looted by the British
                            <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS7484Napier">Napier</persName> expedition in
                            <date>1868</date>.</provenance>
                    </history>
                    
